intermolecular forces. We emphasize the connections among differ-
ent schemes of {DFT} approximations, their underlying assumptions,
and inherent limitations. We also address extensions of equilibrium
{DFT} to phenomenological theories for the dynamic properties of
complex fluids and for the kinetics of phase transitions. In addition,
we highlight the recent literature concerning applications of {DFT}
